    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. York</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 9. 1866/5626</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir/</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With this I send you,<lb/> for publication in the Occident, the<lb/>
                commencement of a translation of<lb/>
                <persName>Dr Philippson's</persName> later &amp; <hi rend="underline">best</hi>
                essay, on<lb/> the trial &amp; condemnation of <persName>Jesus</persName>.<lb/> The
                portion sent is about 1/5 of the whole.<lb/> If that part is not enough for one
                number,<lb/> I can send you more, so as to complete<lb/> the whole in 4 months._</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should you have no use for the<lb/> work, you would greatly oblige
                me<lb/> by returning the M. S._ I desire to<lb/> show you, that I am still willing
                to do<lb/> something for the Occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours, as ever</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">M. Mayer</persName>
            </p>
